<task id="task-4677" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Upgrade checkpoint image quota</title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">A VTP subscription is limited to only 20,000 checkpoint images per month. If you want more image quota, you must upgrade your subscription by following these steps:</context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Sign in to <xref href="https://testops.katalon.io/login" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Katalon TestOps</xref>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the desired Account.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click on the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol> icon, then select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Subscription Management</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Additional Subscription</uicontrol> section, locate your <ph conkeyref="name-variables/visual-testing" class="- topic/ph "/> subscription and click <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">option</i> &gt; <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Upgrade</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp "><image width="700" href="Additional_subscription_-_upgrade_visual_testing.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Additional Subscription - upgrade Visual Testing</alt></image></stepxmp></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the checkout page, input the total number of images you desire, fill in the other required information then enter <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Checkout</uicontrol>.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><note class="- topic/note "><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li ">The number you input must be multiples of 5,000 (e.g., 10,000 images, 15,000 images).</li></ul></note></info></step></steps></taskbody></task>